# Grid regression gate

Read `tools/GRID_REGRESSION.md` before editing grid overlay.

## Required before editing grid

1. Post **Self-Correction Step** per [coding-safety.mdc](../coding-safety.mdc) (regression traps + perf implications + minimal diff).

## Required before marking grid work done

1. Run `.tools/run_grid_smoke.ps1` (or task **grid-smoke**) — must exit 0.
2. Commit **atomic set** together when changing presentation: `.gdshader` + `GridOverlay.gd` + `GridOverlay.tscn` (+ `MainSandbox.gd` if paths/bootstrap change).

## Forbidden

- `git checkout HEAD --` a single grid file without the rest of the atomic set
- Moving `GridOverlay.gd` onto `GridDrawRect` or `GridDisplay`
- Binding `MainSandbox` to `$GridOverlay/GridRect` (use `$GridOverlay` on CanvasLayer)

## WIRING INVARIANT

`GridOverlay.gd` on **CanvasLayer** `$GridOverlay`; shader material on `$GridViewport/GridDrawRect` only; `$GridDisplay` blits cached SubViewport texture.

## Symptom → first check

| Symptom | Check |
|---------|--------|
| Grid missing | `grid.debug_grid_lines` setting; `configure(true)` from MainSandbox |
| Grid static / stale | `apply_view_frame` not called; projection cache not invalidated on resize |
| Idle FPS drop with grid on | `[GridPerf] gpu_refresh_count` should be 0 while idle; SubViewport `UPDATE_ONCE` only on view dirty |
| Shader error | Godot console `SHADER ERROR`; run grid-smoke |
